07/10/2004
PARIS, France -- Kicking off a visit to Paris on Wednesday (6 October), Bulgarian Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg called for the expansion of French investments in his country. 
Addressing a bilateral business forum, he stressed the Bulgarian government's commitment to ensuring transparency, competitiveness and less bureaucracy in the economic sector.
In other news, Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov visits Azerbaijan on Thursday. 
He was in neighbouring Armenia on Wednesday. 
(Bulgarian government Web site, BNR - 06/10/04)
